    "893e1331": {"text":"The road home, with honor in your saddlebags.","hash":"h1-03d19c51"},
    "89417ca9": {"text":"Late study breeds late thoughts. In the margin of an old text you have written something that, read coldly, smells of heresy. Another hand has underlined it.","hash":"h1-e4009a37"},
    "8947272b": {"text":"The old custom names a widow’s third. Their clerks will argue.","hash":"h1-a2e00d70"},
    "894c2935": {"text":"Undermine your rival by fair means or foul.","hash":"h1-4813596b"},
    "89583977": {"text":"{have} of {total} county","hash":"h1-ca797ede"},
    "8960f811": {"text":"Rode to the liege’s war.","hash":"h1-c6557215"},
    "897db875": {"text":"Garlands on the well, a lamb on the spit, and the musicians already flushed with cheer. {province} forgets its burdens for a day.","hash":"h1-f32d4117"},
    "897e9c01": {"text":"Caught lingering behind the arras. The steward’s cuff rings your ear.","hash":"h1-7e21b1ab"},
